Package betsy.vocab

Has classes used to interpret the meaning of words and their different forms.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    WordInfo
    The WordInfo info interface describes a single word.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdjectiveInfo
    A WordInfo describing an adjective.
    AdverbInfo
    A WordInfo describing an adverb.
    GenericWordInfo
    A generic implementation of WordInfo.
    Names
    The names class has static methods and variables that keep track of lists of common male/female first names.
    NounInfo
    A WordInfo describing a noun.
    VerbInfo
    A WordInfo describing a verb.
    Vocab
    A collection of methods used for analyzing single words.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AdjectiveInfo.AdjectiveType
    An adjective can be: NORMAL: "fast" COMPARATIVE: "faster" SUPERLATIVE: "fastest"
    VerbInfo.VerbType
    Describes the tense of a verb, including its time and frame.
